<section class="py-24 bg-[#111111]">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#C9A84C] mb-8 leading-tight">
      The Problem
    </h2>
    <div class="space-y-6 text-[#9CA3AF] text-lg leading-relaxed border-l-2 border-[#C9A84C]/30 pl-8">
      <p>
        You're running a real business with real crews, real clients, and real deadlines. Somewhere along the way, you ended up managing 12 different software subscriptions, a dozen spreadsheets, and a team that spends half its day copy-pasting information between tools.
      </p>
      <p>
        The software was supposed to make things easier. It didn't. It just added more screens to check and more things to update manually.
      </p>
      <p>
        You're paying for tools nobody fully uses, chasing down paperwork that should write itself, and wondering why you're still doing the same manual tasks you were doing five years ago.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[#F0F0F0] font-semibold text-xl">
        There's a better way to set this up.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
